{This chapter analyses the main line in the course as it deals with White's strongest and most natural plan of capturing on d5 , followed up by the attack on the queen on d5 with Nc3 .} 1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 {White's most natural move, developing the knight and attacking the queen on d5 .} Qd8 {The queen returns home to the safest spot. Black will now continue with development ... c6 , ... Bf5 and ... e6 , to set up 'the saw' - the black pawns on c6 and e6 with the light-squared bishop active on f5 . There are certain details when it comes to the move order of achieving 'the saw' so these should be carefully taken into consideration.} 4. d4 {Again the most natural move for White, taking up central space.} c6 {Black prepares 'the saw' by controlling the d5 -square with the pawn on c6 . Next the bishop will be developed to f5 after which 'the saw' will be complete after ... e6 .} 5. d5 {This is a concrete move worth mentioning. It's an impatient move where White seeks immediate clarification in the centre. Not surprisingly, it gives Black an easy game.} Nf6 {It's also possible to capture on d5 , but it's more ambitious to develop the knight and attack the pawn on d5 .} 6. Bc4 ({White clings onto the pawn on d5 . The exchange of queens after} 6. dxc6 Qxd1+ 7. Nxd1 Nxc6 {is excellent for Black, who already has a development advantage.}) 6... cxd5 {This is the simplest solution. After the mass exchanges on d5 Black obtains a comfortable endgame.} 7. Nxd5 {The exchanges on d5 are inevitable.} Nxd5 {Black continues exchanging.} 8. Qxd5 ({Capturing with the bishop won't change much after} 8. Bxd5 e6 9. Bf3 Qxd1+ 10. Bxd1 Bc5 {, with a similar endgame.}) 8... Qxd5 {White was threatening Qxf7 , so the exchange of queens is forced.} 9. Bxd5 e6 {Chasing away the enemy bishop and opening the diagonal for the dark-squared bishop.} 10. Bf3 Bc5 {Black will finish the development of all the pieces with ... Nc6 , ... Ke7 , ... Bd7 when the general plan will be to combine the advance of the central pawns with activity on the queenside.} *

